summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about barley yields

properties.description: The yield of barley in bushels per acre
The year in which the barley was grown

goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving an idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?
goals.visualization: violin plot of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A violin plot can show the distribution of yield for each variety, allowing for comparison of the central tendency and spread of the data across different categories.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield across different sites?
goals.rationale: A histogram can show the frequency distribution of yield for each site, allowing for comparison of the yield distribution across different locations.

goals.question: How does the yield vary between the two years in the dataset?
goals.visualization: box plot of yield by year
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution for each year, allowing for comparison of the central tendency and spread of the data between the two years.

goals.question: What is the relationship between yield and location?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of yield by site
goals.rationale: A scatter plot can show the relationship between yield and location, allowing for identification of any patterns or trends in the data.

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.boxplot(data['yield'])
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Yield (bushels per acre)')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.violinplot(x='variety', y='yield', data=data, palette='Set3')
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Barley Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Yield (bushels per acre)')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    data.groupby('site')['yield'].plot(kind='hist', alpha=0.5, ax=ax, legend=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Yield')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of yield across different sites?')
    ax.legend(data['site'].unique())
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = data['year'].astype(str)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['year'] == '1931']['yield'], data[data['year'] == '1932']['yield']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['1931', '1932'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield (bushels/acre)')
    plt.title('How does the yield vary between the two years in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['site'], data['yield'])
    plt.xlabel('Site')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between yield and location?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
